# File Size Limit & Modularization Rules

- If a file exceeds 300 lines, you MUST NOT edit it without first identifying parts to extract into separate modules.
- Before editing a large file, propose which parts (e.g., Page Objects, helpers, fixtures, types) should be moved to dedicated files.
- Aim for small, focused files that are easier to maintain and consume fewer tokens.
- When refactoring, maintain the same functionality while improving structure.
- **NEVER create new files >300 lines.**
- **If you find a "monster" (>500 lines) and need to work with it, you MUST first plan its decomposition.**